        <h1>Saving Tigers in India</h1>
        <p>A Global Responsibility</p>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section id="problem">
            <h2>The Problem</h2>
            <p>Mining, deforestation, and habitat fragmentation in India threaten tiger populations. This has global repercussions, including on biodiversity and climate resilience.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="solutions">
            <h2>Solutions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>CSR-Driven Habitat Restoration:</strong> Reforestation and wildlife corridors.</li>
                <li><strong>Eco-Tourism:</strong> Sustainable tourism benefiting local communities.</li>
                <li><strong>Technological Advances:</strong> AI and drones for tracking and anti-poaching.</li>
                <li><strong>Triple Bottom Line:</strong> Integrating people, planet, and profit.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="visuals">
            <h2>Visual Insights</h2>
            <img src="tiger-trends-graph.jpg" alt="Tiger population trends graph">
            <img src="csr-pie-chart.jpg" alt="CSR investment pie chart">
        </section>
        <section id="impact">
            <h2>Global Impact</h2>
            <p>Effective tiger conservation in India supports international biodiversity treaties, benefiting global ecosystems and economic stability.</p>
        </section>
